      "id": 9,
      "options": {
        "content": "## Key Finding: HYPE Trades Too Infrequently\n\n**The Problem**: After a large order, the average time to the next trade is **~130 seconds** (2+ minutes). This means:\n- You can't quickly enter a fade position\n- By the time the next trade happens, the \"reversion window\" may have passed\n- Only ~60% of large orders have a trade within 1 minute to measure\n\n**Implication**: Even if reversion exists, it's not actionable on HYPE due to low liquidity/frequency.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Key Finding",
      "type": "text"
    }
